<font color="#FF0000">BARBARIANS AT THE GATE</font><br>
<tt>Sat Aug 30 23:10:17 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
For a long time this site held to high standards, of intellectual discourse, of emotional healing, of the likes of Tanker, DocDel, Chet, Professor, and others, many others.<br>
We fought out our boundaries and established our positions. We gradually learned to learn from each other, and to respect each other.We shared our feelings and we grew.  <br><br>
Then, like a virus, the site got invaded and changed. Code names replaced real ideas. Gory stories replaced emotional release. Macho braggards replaced sincere veterans. Bullshit replaced real emotions.  Brave names and secred codes replaced open honesty and men brave enough to talk about their guts.<br><br>
Is this the normal cycle of a site? I don't know.  It is like we started out with praise and poetry, emotions and depth, and ended up at the wrong end of Conan the Barbarian.<br>
I grieve for the former, and I am repulsed by the latter.<br><br>
The fact that one of the most prominent writers now has his own agenda, I mean book and it is so obvious. Others have their native roots to push. Some can't stand alone and are doomed to flip-flop back and forth.  But above all, or possibly below all, is the tune: &quot;Macho Macho man, I want to be a Macho man.&quot;<br><br>
We used to have a site of sharing, of healing, of growing. Now we have a site of gory, of murder, of killing &quot;gooks&quot; and &quot;commies&quot; and we have lost something with this new generation of &quot;posters.&quot;  We have lost the ability of critical thinking. Of daring to think differently. Of questioning authority and the established norm.  Of dropping the &quot;commie bull shit line&quot; and moving beyond it. We used to have Vietnamese contributors, now they have headed for the hills, or their bunkers, knowing that this site in now hostile for them.<br><br>
As a result, we have lost most of our original writers. Gone is DocDel, Tanker, Sarge666, most of Chet, and many, many others.  I understand that they don't want to wallow in the mud with the new boys. That is their right, and I respect it. I just pine for it.<br><br>
It just is a damn shame to see the site change this way. Perhaps it had to. Perhaps Kali Tai and her bullshit site will reigh supreme after all (sixties-L project). But before the magic names and Indian hoo-rah, before the macho &quot;kill the commies&quot; jargon, there once was a place of feelings, of raw emotions, like real group therapy, where one could talk and dump, and no-one stuck him in the side with a pig sticker, and the group encouraged him to continue.  Now the site is more a battle field.  Not a therapy group or a meeting of old friends.  I am so sorry for this turn of events, even though I didn't start it, couldn't stop it,<br>
 and wish to hell it never happened.<br><br>
All I can do is call upon the old posters, the old writers, to get involved again. Stem the tide brothers and SISTERS. (I know you are out there sisters, I hope you have not fled). Reclaim our land, our land.  We don't have to give up in silence.  Express your disgust and light up this site.  This is our last stand, before the hordes of the barbarians blow open our gate.  Who will stand with me?  Will you not join me in a site for sharing of feelings, instead of bragging about killing, of growth, instead of death?  Come on Lads and Lassies, the time is nigh, and there is work aplenty.
<p><code>-- posted  (doc spatz) </code><p>


